cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.NE 

This paper discusses the design and implementation of a hybrid neural network for logical learning, which involves the use of auxiliary inputs to suggest logical outcomes. This topic is closely related to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI), as well as computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO) since the paper mentions an application in an autonomous grasping robot. Additionally, the use of neural networks suggests a connection to neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
